Two U.S. states, [[Minnesota]] and [[Oregon]], have officially declared a '''state mushroom'''. Minnesota was the first to declare a species; ''[[Morchella esculenta]]'' was chosen as its state mushroom in 1984, and codified into Statute in 2010.<ref name="Minnesota"/> A third state, [[Missouri]], has had a state mushroom proposed. __TOC__ {{clear}}
